title: The Polarization Powers of The Average Atomic Weight Nuclei for 1.5 Mev Neutrons

x4freetext: THE POLARIZATION POWERS OF THE AVERAGE ATOMIC WEIGHT

x4codes.hlp: Inst. Fiziki A.N. Ukrainskoi SSR, Kiev, Union of Soviet Socialist Republics

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Izv. Rossiiskoi Akademii Nauk, Ser.Fiz., Vol.35, Issue.4, p.823 (1971)
Rept: Yaderno-Fizicheskie Issledovaniya v SSSR, No.10, p.50 (1970)

x4freetext: DIFFERENTIAL ELASTIC SCATTERING CROSS SECTIONS WERE
MEASURED ABSOLUTELY. THE POLARISATION DUE TO SCATTERING
WAS DEFINED SUPPOSING THE T(PN)-REACTION NEUTRON
POLARISATION EQUAL 36+-2 PERCENT  AT AN ANGLE OF 33
DEGREES FOR 1.5 MEV NEUTRONS,ACCORDING TO KELSEY C.A.
DIFFERENTIAL ELASTIC SCATTERING CROSS SECTIONS WERE
MEASURED  USING THE CYLINDRICAL GEOMETRY. THE
POLARIZATION DUE TO SCATTERING WAS MEASURED BY THE
HOLLOW CYLINDERS, L=6 CM, D1=3 CM, D2=0.6-1 CM.
DIFFERENTIAL CROSS SECTIONS WERE CORRECTED FOR THE FLUX
ABSORPTION AND MULTIPLE SCATTERING IN THE SAMPLE.
POLARIZATION WAS CORRECTED FOR THE MULTIPLE SCATTERING.
QUOTED ELASTIC SCATTERING POLARIZATION ERRORS ARE
STATISTICAL ERRORS ARISING WHEN MEASURING ASIMMETRY.
STATISTICAL ERRORS OF THE DIFFERENTIAL CROSS SECTIONS
AUTHOR NAME AND REACTION CODES CORRECTOD
